She shook her head, &quot;No, not really....you're the one that was making all the promises back there. You tell me..where we're going.&quot; The blonde pulled out of the dhampire's embrace, turning to look her in the eye. Taylee wasn't about to let Rayne in on any of her safe places. If the girl wanted Taylee along so bad she could share some of her secrets.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=midnightrayne>Midnight Rayne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mistress of Blood</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#8B4513>(10/6/03 9:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkalaberiafrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://forumshomepage.homestead.com/files/midnightrayne.jpg height=200 WIDTH=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Home Sweet Home</span><hr size=1> I stepped up close to Taylee as she turned to face me and look me in the eye. It did not seem as though she was challenging me but it was just my habit to act like she was. My breath was hot on her face as I stood very close, my lips almost brushing hers. &quot;So... I did make promises...&quot; I whispered as I placed my hands on my slender hips. &quot;And I always keep them unless released from them...&quot;I teasingly directed my breath across the side of her neck.<br>
<br>
&quot;As for someplace to go... well we are in the harbour area and surrounded by vampire lairs. I suggest we go more into the city and away from here. That of course means that we won't be returning here when we are done.&quot; I looked her in the eye and slipped both my hands on her waist with a smirk on my lips. &quot;I did offer my safe house earlier and we could always go there... Actually we'll have to go there.&quot;<br>
<br>
With a toss of my head to the side, I stepped backwards and away from her slowly. This was her last chance to go back inside or come with me as I turned and began to walk slowly down the street. In my area there was food stores for mortals, protected by high security so as to not become vampire feeding grounds but I knew I would find something to eat there. Even with the high security, a vampire or two always hung about and I was planning on killing one while Taylee went grocery shopping. It was a great plan and then we'd go back to my place for a better place to stay then something so run down as George's place.<br>
<br>
&quot;So... coming?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=taylea>Taylea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silent Beauty
