<br>
Rayne mentioned her safe house before stepping away, and Taylee had to agree, although silently, that it was probably the best place to go right now. It had to be better then where they were now.Taylee watched as Rayne started to walk down the street, before the dhampire stopped, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;So... coming?&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
A smirk crossed Taylee's face. &quot;Well I don't have any other plans tonight,&quot; she replied with a bit of a sarcastic edge, before a laugh escaped, &quot;So...why not.&quot; The blonde girl glanced back to where she knew George must still be working, a twinge of regret flowing through her. 'But,' she told herself, 'I'll most likely run into him again sometime.'<br>
<br>
Throwing her damp jacket over her shoulders, Taylee hurried to catch up with Rayne, who was waiting, almost patiently. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=midnightrayne>Midnight Rayne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mistress of Blood</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#8B4513>(10/9/03 7:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkalaberiafrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://forumshomepage.homestead.com/files/midnightrayne.jpg height=200 WIDTH=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Home Sweet Home</span><hr size=1> &quot;Ohhh sarcasm... girl I love you already.&quot; I smirked as Taylee caught up to me. She had some fire in her and I liked that, there just might be hope for this girl yet. With a one finger salute of farewell to George's rundown home, I turned with Taylee and continued on our way out of the area. Since I knew the city somewhat, mainly by landscapes, it was going to be easy enough to find my way back home. With the memory of recient events however I was more then satisfied to stick to the streets.<br>
<br>
My weapons in plain sight probably kept away anyone that might have seen us and wanted some trouble because Taylee and I encountered very little on the way back through the city. It was a long walk however and I was amazed that the little shit George could have gotten Taylee and the baby through the sewers this distance so quickly. I kept a watchful on our surroundings as we walked, noticing more familer locations as Taylee and I progressed further back into the city.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hey you know...&quot; I licked my lips lightly. &quot;Those vampires that played with you earlier. I could always go kick their ass for you. It would be fun and I could always use a good fight.&quot; I looked at Taylee as we walked down a street not far from the grocery store. Of course we wouldn't need to go there tonight, I wanted to eat and go home first for a while. But since it seemed Taylee would be my guest for a while, we had to do something. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=taylea>Taylea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silent Beauty
