<br>
Taylee heard Rayne mention going after the vampires that she'd seen earlier, and as the redhead looked over at her, a feeling of dread washed through her. Taking a steadying breath, she looked back at Rayne, &quot;I-I don't think that would b a good idea. Cale isn't someone you should mess with, and I'd rather he didn't know where I was.&quot; Taylee shrugged, &quot;The woman...I don't know who she was, so I guess she's fair game.&quot;<br>
<br>
Just thinking about Cale made Taylee scared, and she began to look in the shadows as they walked. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=midnightrayne>Midnight Rayne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mistress of Blood</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#8B4513>(10/11/03 7:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkalaberiafrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://forumshomepage.homestead.com/files/midnightrayne.jpg height=200 WIDTH=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Home Sweet Home</span><hr size=1> &quot;Fuck Cale... stupid prick.&quot; Rayne muttered aloud as she glanced into the shadows as Taylee did. &quot;That guy couldn't find an asshole in a group of gay men... and besides, if you think he's something kinda wonderful...&quot; the dhampire licked her lips as she looked back at the blonde seductivly. &quot;You haven't seen me in action yet.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;And stop worrying about the shadows hun, I can hear and see anything that hides there unless they have the ability to hide their thoughts or hide their form in shadow.&quot; she smirked as she clicked and unclicked her weapons dangerously in as Taylee assumed, a 'don't fuck with me' additude. She liked these deserted streets but as they neared the populated sector, more and more people could be seen. The two made an odd looking couple, drawing attention to themselves by Rayne's show of weapons. The grocery store was still a few blocks ahead of them though when Rayne came to a stop and turned to face Taylee. It was time to go their seporate ways for the moment and Rayne had a very good idea. It least in her own opinion that is.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ok Taylee, here is the deal... You need food as do I and there is always vampires lurking in the shadows around the market.&quot; Rayne began to lay out her plan. &quot;You need the food on the inside, I need the food on the outside so here is the set up. I'll sneek around outside and find a vampire, you go inside and get your food. Once your done, I'll tell you telepathicly where I am and you come this way. We'll lead the vampire into a quiet place, I'll slay it and then we both go on our way to my safe house.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;And if you have any problems with being the bait, well you won't be in any harm because I do not want to be harmed either. We'll be finding a lone vampire and I am sure you'd rather I kill it out of the way of mortals to spare them the harm they would recieve if they got in the way...&quot; Rayne placed her hands on her hips as she stood with one lfoot before the other. &quot;Unless you have other ideas? Another blood source?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=taylea>Taylea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silent Beauty
